    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Oil Temperature (EOT) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f2650211003" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>EOT sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The EOT sensor, a thermistor sensor, detects engine oil temperature.</para>
        <para>The EOT signal is monitored by the ECM for EGR valve, VGT, and for engine fueling calculations. The EOT
            signal allows the ECM to compensate for differences in oil viscosity, due to temperature changes.
        </para>
        <para>The EOT sensor is installed in the rear of the front cover, on the intake side of the engine.</para>
    </svcproc>
